## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="22d83-102">這個類別包含單字與片語在語音辨識作業，包括下列所處理的詳細的資訊：</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-102">This class contains detailed information about words and phrases processed during speech recognition operations, including the following:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="22d83-103"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Grammar%2A>屬性參考<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar>辨識器用來識別輸入。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-103">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Grammar%2A> property references the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> that the recognizer used to identify the input.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="22d83-104"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Text%2A>屬性包含片語的正規化的文字。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-104">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Text%2A> property contains the normalized text for the phrase.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="22d83-105"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Semantics%2A>屬性參考包含在結果中語意資訊。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-105">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Semantics%2A> property references the semantic information contained in the result.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-106">語意資訊是索引鍵名稱和相關聯的語意資料的字典。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-106">The semantic information is a dictionary of the key names and associated semantic data.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="22d83-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Words%2A>屬性包含的已排序的集合<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit>物件代表每個辨識輸入中的文字。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-107">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Words%2A> property contains an ordered collection of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit> objects that represent each recognized word in the input.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-108">每個 word 單位包含顯示格式、 語彙格式，以及相對應的文字的發音資訊。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-108">Each word unit contains display format, lexical format, and pronunciation information for the corresponding word.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="22d83-109"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.ReplacementWordUnits%2A>屬性包含特定字組替代的相關資訊。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-109">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.ReplacementWordUnits%2A> property contains information about specialized word substitution.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="22d83-110"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Homophones%2A>和<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.HomophoneGroupId%2A>屬性包含相同或類似發音的辨識替代項目的相關資訊。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-110">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Homophones%2A> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.HomophoneGroupId%2A> properties contain information about recognition alternates that have the same or similar pronunciation.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="22d83-111">值<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A>屬性會指出確定性，語音辨識器所指派的已辨識的片語與輸入相符程度。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-111">The value of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Confidence%2A> property  indicates the degree of certainty, assigned by the speech recognizer, that a recognized phrase matches the input.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="22d83-112">語音辨識器傳回在辨識結果<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>物件，繼承自<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-112">The speech recognizer returns recognition results in a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult> object, which inherits from <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-113">辨識結果<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A>屬性包含的已排序的集合<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>物件，每個都是針對至辨識器輸入可能相符項目。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-113">The recognition result <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A> property contains an ordered collection of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> objects, each of which is a possible match for the input to the recognizer.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="22d83-114">下列範例示範的處理常式<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType>， <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType>，或<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType>事件，以及一些相關聯的資訊<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>物件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-114">The following example shows a handler for a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType>, or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType> event and some of the information associated with the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-115"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult> 類別衍生自 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> 類別。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-115">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult> class derives from the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> class.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
void SpeechRecognizedHandler(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
{  
  if (e.Result == null) return;  
  
  // Add event handler code here.  
  
  // The following code illustrates some of the information available  
  // in the recognition result.  
  Console.WriteLine("Recognition result summary:");  
  Console.WriteLine(  
    "  Recognized phrase: {0}\n" +   
    "  Confidence score {1}\n" +   
    "  Grammar used: {2}\n",   
    e.Result.Text, e.Result.Confidence, e.Result.Grammar.Name);  
  
  // Display the semantic values in the recognition result.  
  Console.WriteLine("  Semantic results:");  
  foreach (KeyValuePair<String, SemanticValue> child in e.Result.Semantics)  
  {  
    Console.WriteLine("    The {0} city is {1}",  
      child.Key, child.Value.Value ?? "null");  
  }  
  Console.WriteLine();  
  
  // Display information about the words in the recognition result.  
  Console.WriteLine("  Word summary: ");  
  foreach (RecognizedWordUnit word in e.Result.Words)  
  {  
    Console.WriteLine(  
      "    Lexical form ({1})" +  
      " Pronunciation ({0})" +  
      " Display form ({2})",  
      word.Pronunciation, word.LexicalForm, word.DisplayAttributes);  
  }  
  
  // Display information about the audio in the recognition result.  
  Console.WriteLine("  Input audio summary:\n" +  
    "    Candidate Phrase at:       {0} mSec\n" +  
    "    Phrase Length:             {1} mSec\n" +  
    "    Input State Time:          {2}\n" +  
    "    Input Format:              {3}\n",  
    e.Result.Audio.AudioPosition,  
    e.Result.Audio.Duration,  
    e.Result.Audio.StartTime,  
    e.Result.Audio.Format.EncodingFormat);  
  
  // Display information about the alternate recognitions in the recognition result.  
  Console.WriteLine("  Alternate phrase collection:");  
  foreach (RecognizedPhrase phrase in e.Result.Alternates)  
  {  
    Console.WriteLine("    Phrase: " + phrase.Text);  
    Console.WriteLine("    Confidence score: " + phrase.Confidence);  
  }  
}  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="22d83-119">信心分數並不表示絕對正確辨識片語的可能性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-119">Confidence scores do not indicate the absolute likelihood that a phrase was recognized correctly.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-120">相反地，信心分數會提供一種機制，來比較多的辨識替代項目針對指定輸入的準確度。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-120">Instead, confidence scores provide a mechanism for comparing the relative accuracy of multiple recognition alternates for a given input.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-121">這有助於最精確的辨識結果傳回。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-121">This facilitates returning the most accurate recognition result.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-122">例如，如果已辨識的片語的信心分數為 0.8，這不表示片語，有 80%可能是輸入正確的相符項目。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-122">For example, if a recognized phrase has a confidence score of 0.8, this does not mean that the phrase has an 80% chance of being the correct match for the input.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="22d83-123">表示一詞是更有可能是其他有信心的結果比輸入正確的相符項目率小於 0.8。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-123">It means that the phrase is more likely to be the correct match for the input than other results that have confidence scores less than 0.8.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="22d83-124">信心分數本身不具意義，除非您有要比較，從相同的辨識作業，或是從相同的輸入的前一項辨識替代結果。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-124">A confidence score on its own is not meaningful unless you have alternative results to compare against, either from the same recognition operation or from previous recognitions of the same input.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-125">值用來排名替代的候選項目所傳回的片語<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A>屬性上的<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>物件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-125">The values are used to rank alternative candidate phrases returned by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A> property on <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult> objects.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="22d83-126">信賴值為相對且唯一到每個辨識引擎。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-126">Confidence values are relative and unique to each recognition engine.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-127">不能有意義地比較兩個不同的辨識引擎所傳回的信心值。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-127">Confidence values returned by two different recognition engines cannot be meaningfully compared.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="22d83-128">語音辨識引擎可能會將低的信心分數指派給語音輸入，基於各種原因，包括背景干擾、 inarticulate 語音或非預期的字或文字序列。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-128">A speech recognition engine may assign a low confidence score to spoken input for various reasons, including background interference, inarticulate speech, or unanticipated words or word sequences.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-129">如果您的應用程式使用<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>執行個體，您可以修改在哪一個語音輸入接受或拒絕使用其中一個的信賴等級<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.UpdateRecognizerSetting%2A>方法。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-129">If your application is using a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> instance, you can modify the confidence level at which speech input is accepted or rejected with one of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.UpdateRecognizerSetting%2A> methods.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-130">共用辨識器所管理的信賴度臨界值<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer>是使用者設定檔相關聯，儲存在 Windows 登錄中。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-130">Confidence thresholds for the shared recognizer, managed by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer>, are associated with a user profile and stored in the Windows registry.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-131">應用程式不應該寫入登錄中的共用辨識器的屬性變更。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-131">Applications should not write changes to the registry for the properties of the shared recognizer.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="22d83-132"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A>的屬性<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>物件包含的已排序的集合<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>物件，每個都是針對至辨識器輸入可能相符項目。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-132">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult.Alternates%2A> property of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult> object contains an ordered collection of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> objects, each of which is a possible match for the input to the recognizer.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-133">替代項目會從最高至最低的信賴度排列。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-133">The alternates are ordered from highest to lowest confidence.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="22d83-134">下列範例示範的處理常式<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType>， <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType>，或<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType>事件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-134">The following example shows a handler for a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType>, or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType> event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-135">此範例示範資訊與相關聯<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>物件，其中有些衍生自<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-135">The example shows information associated with the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult> object, some of which is derived from <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="22d83-136">這個處理常式會顯示已辨識片語也與辨識替代項目的的信心分數。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="22d83-136">The handler displays confidence scores for a recognized phrase as well as for recognition alternates.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
void SpeechRecognizedHandler(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
{  
  if (e.Result == null) return;  
  
  // Add event handler code here.  
  
  // The following code illustrates some of the information available  
  // in the recognition result.  
  Console.WriteLine("Recognition result summary:");  
  Console.WriteLine(  
    "  Recognized phrase: {0}\n" +   
    "  Confidence score {1}\n" +   
    "  Grammar used: {2}\n",   
    e.Result.Text, e.Result.Confidence, e.Result.Grammar.Name);  
  
  // Display the semantic values in the recognition result.  
  Console.WriteLine("  Semantic results:");  
  foreach (KeyValuePair<String, SemanticValue> child in e.Result.Semantics)  
  {  
    Console.WriteLine("    The {0} city is {1}",  
      child.Key, child.Value.Value ?? "null");  
  }  
  Console.WriteLine();  
  
  // Display information about the words in the recognition result.  
  Console.WriteLine("  Word summary: ");  
  foreach (RecognizedWordUnit word in e.Result.Words)  
  {  
    Console.WriteLine(  
      "    Lexical form ({1})" +  
      " Pronunciation ({0})" +  
      " Display form ({2})",  
      word.Pronunciation, word.LexicalForm, word.DisplayAttributes);  
  }  
  
  // Display information about the audio in the recognition result.  
  Console.WriteLine("  Input audio summary:\n" +  
    "    Candidate Phrase at:       {0} mSec\n" +  
    "    Phrase Length:             {1} mSec\n" +  
    "    Input State Time:          {2}\n" +  
    "    Input Format:              {3}\n",  
    e.Result.Audio.AudioPosition,  
    e.Result.Audio.Duration,  
    e.Result.Audio.StartTime,  
    e.Result.Audio.Format.EncodingFormat);  
  
  // Display information about the alternate recognitions in the recognition result.  
  Console.WriteLine("  Alternate phrase collection:");  
  foreach (RecognizedPhrase phrase in e.Result.Alternates)  
  {  
    Console.WriteLine("    Phrase: " + phrase.Text);  
    Console.WriteLine("    Confidence score: " + phrase.Confidence);  
  }  
